    "121883833": {
      "title": "A Lower Bound for the Smallest Singular Value of a Matrix",
      "abstract": "Abstract For a matrix A which is diagonally dominant both by rows and by columns, we give bounds for ‖A-1‖1 and ‖A-1‖∞, which then can be used to give a lower bound for the smallest singular value. We also show that these bounds can be attained, and show how the result can be extended to block matrices."
